    "Image segmentation could be divided into two sub-tasks: semantic segmentation, instance segmentation, and panoptic segmentation shown in Fig. 4.",
    "Semantic segmentation is used to classify each pixel in the image, whereas instance segmentation classifies each object in the image and panoptic segmentation is a combination of both semantic and instance segmentation.",
    "In this section, a detailed description for semantic, instance and panoptic segmentation is given.",
    "ACM 6 Nature 6 MDPI 5 Wiley 2 Hindawi 1 Others 14 Elsevier 25 Arxiv 10 Springer 28",
    "The term instance segmentation refers to the assignment of different labels to different instances of an object belonging to the same class."
